<br>
She dismounted her horse, and walked through the village. Most of the huts were torn down, broken swords, chobos, daggers, and spears were scattered about everywhere. It had looked like there had been a war.<br>
<br>
Odessa found her way to the Queen's hut, and took a deep breath as she entered. It looked like it had been well guarded, seeing as it was the only hut that hadn't been damaged. The Ceremonial Mask of the Queen had been left on the bed; along with a scroll. She picked up the scroll, and read it.<br>
<br>
&quot;To my fellow Athelfi,<br>
This tribe was attacked by a group of renegade Centaurs after the Amazon/Centaur war had been won by the Amazons. We were few in numbers, and were easy prey for the vast majourity of these demons. Most of my tribe was all but gone, leaving me a Queen without a tribe. Whoever finds this scroll, I leave this village to you. I have faith in you Athelfi, faith that you'd build Paphos up again and to make it a glorious tribe of Amazons.<br>
<br>
Efharisto and Herete,<br>
<br>
Vasilissa Thalestris.&quot;<br>
<br>
Odessa bowed her head, saying a small prayer for the Amazons that have gone on. Even though Odessa was a Scynthian Amazon, she had great respect for the Goddess Artemis, and seeing as this land was on Greek Amazon Territory, she would repsect the lands and their customs. But, she knew every tribe had their own customs; she would hope that she could bring the ways of the Scynthians to Greece, but still uphold both Greecian and Scynthian Amazon standards.<br>
<br>
She exited the hut, the mask in her hands. She looked toward the North, and knelt on one knee.<br>
<br>
&quot;Atmah, please watch over these fallen Amazons. Even though they are not Scynthians, they still were our Athelfi.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then moved over to where the direction of Mount Olympus was, and bowed her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Artemis, these Amazons were loyal to you...even in death. Please, remember them and honour them...for even in death; they are our Athelfi.&quot;<br>
<br>
Odessa stood and held the Amazon Mask high in the air, letting out a War Cry.<br>
 <p>~ Odessa Sayler Loire ~
