<br>
Belle dismounted the tall blonde mare, the same horse she'd been given nearly a year ago for her fifteenth. <br>
<br>
A defined brow arched slightly as she heard the warcry, and blue eyes finally shifted towards the abandoned village.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gods... what happened here?&quot; she muttered to herself with wide eyes, a soft undertone of a sigh carrying through.<br>
<br>
Biting her lower lip gently, she took a few slow, cautious steps into the lands. It was easy to tell there'd been a war, and she took a moment to bow her head in respect to those whose lives were lost, and say a silent prayer to the Atmah Cyane, before approaching Odessa.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's going on, athelfi?&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessasaylerloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa Sayler Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 3:08 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/chakram-amarice01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Odessa turned to Belle, and sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;This village was destroyed by renegade centaurs after the war. After the war, there were only a handful of Amazons left, and then they came...wiping them out but one or two and the Vasilissa.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked down to the Mask.<br>
<br>
&quot;She left a scroll, wanting whoever found it to be Queen of Paphos, to make Paphos what it was before they were wiped out.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked to the mask again, and then to Belle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Prigkipissa, I know Scynthia is my home and I know that eggonaki materas is my original Vasilissa, but...this fallen tribe needs someone to re-establish this place. Even though I'm not a Greek Amazon by birth, I am a Scynthian Amazon...and I know the Atmah would want me to do this...&quot; <p>~ Odessa Sayler Loire ~
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ubelleevandaloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belle EvandaLoire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 3:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Belle starred at her for a moment, rather speechless. This was sort of sudden, wasn't it? Could Odessa really do this?<br>
<br>
Then she smiled lightly, letting her eyes swipe unhurriedly over the village, picturing just what it could be restored to.<br>
<br>
&quot;The Atmah led you here, Dess. You're right. She'd want you to honor a last queen's wishes... Mother'd be proud.&quot;<br>
<br>
She paused, glancing around the disarrayed area once more.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know if you heard, but Aliya's very sick... I'm devoting most of my time to keeping her company while she's bedridden, but once she gets better,&quot; Belle refused to even acknowledge another option, &quot;I'll help out as best I can.&quot;<br>
 <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessasaylerloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa Sayler Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 5:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/chakram-amarice01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Odessa bowed her head and then looked to Belle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aunt Aliya? I'll visit her as soon as I can...&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked toward the Horizon.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know I can do this...this was why I was born, to become a Queen...I have so much in store for me, Belle, I don't want to disappoint anyone...&quot;<br>
<br>
She wondered what her mother and Grandmother would say. <p>~ Odessa Sayler Loire ~
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ubelleevandaloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belle EvandaLoire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 9:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> &quot;Don't worry about letting anyone down.&quot;<br>
<br>
She, too, wondered briefly just what Cora and Alysia would have to say... She knew they'd support her, of course. But after how much convincing?<br>
<br>
&quot;Just focus on you, and do this for yourself, the Vasilissa who left the tribe to you, and the fallen athelfi who were killed here. I have faith in you, and so does everyone else.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled encouragingly as she took one more glance around the village. It wouldn't be so hard to rebuild, really. Just a little hard work. Maybe Odessa really could handle this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessasaylerloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa Sayler Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 9:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/chakram-amarice01.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Joint Post with Cora</span><hr size=1> How Cora manages to get around, nobody knows. She just got skills. Being the swift creature she was raised to be, she emerged from.. somewhere.. behind Odessa and placed a hand on her daughter's shoulder. Somehow, she managed to seem taller and more regal -- like back in the days when she too was an important Amazon figure.<br>
<br>
&quot;It was long decreed, Odessa. I feel I have done my part. I gave you the gifts that were passed on to me, and then allowed you to be raised by your grandmother, who I knew would bring you to greatness.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leaning, Cora kissed Odessa's temple and whispered. &quot;Remember -- tikon e terent (honor and trust). I believe in you.&quot;<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Odessa smiled to Belle and then blinked at her mother.<br>
<br>
&quot;M...Materas?&quot;<br>
<br>
She hugged her and listened to what her mother had to say.<br>
Odessa smiled, wiping the tears from her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nai, Materas, Efharisto.&quot;<br>
<br>
She thought highly of what her family had to say, especially her mother and grandmother. <p>~ Odessa Sayler Loire ~
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 386<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/18/02 9:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Alysia smiled as she stood in the doorway. Please, did you really think something this big could happen and the Atmah wouldn't let Aly know about it? <br>
<br>
She smiled to both of them.<br>
<br>
&quot;She's right Odessa. I have faith in you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alysia knew that there were many fallen tribes that Odessa would come across on her journeys. But never did she expect this. <br>
<br>
&quot;Many young Queens are rising in the Nation. I was only twenty. Lilla Darkshade is young as well but she shall bring Orio-Pata up well. Raven of the Tanias Valley is only seventeen as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled. She knew Odessa could do this.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have the blood of the Ancients in you Odessa. I have planned for many years for you to take your riteful place in the Nation, and now you shall . . . as Queen.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessasaylerloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa Sayler Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/19/02 1:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A New Vasilissa</span><hr size=1> Odessa turned to Aly, and smiled as she hugged her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Efharisto&gt;&quot;<br>
<br>
She knew Aly would make it, she knew the Atmah had told her before hand. She smiled, looking down.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know the Atmah led me here, but...there's still so much for me to learn and to know before I officially come Queen.&quot;<br>
<br>
That was right, just because the old Queen was passing on her Rite of Caste to Odessa, she'd have to wait for an official coronation; and that was something she was willing to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 389<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/19/02 11:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Things to do</span><hr size=1> Alysia smiled returning the hug.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes my little kouri. There is much to do.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled both to her and Belle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Odessa, settle yourself here as well as you can. Make a home of these lands for they belong to you now.&quot;<br>
<br>
She reached into her pockey handing her a medallion very similar to the Loire one she already wore. Only this one was different. It was a Tretmolec Medallion.<br>
<br>
&quot;Keep this with you always, and you shall forever carry the Atmah with you. She shall be your guide. Within the next moon, return to Scynthia, where I shall reveal my long awaited plans for you both.&quot; She glanced to Belle also.<br>
<br>
&quot;Until then, I will not leave you alone here.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turned revealing a large white wolf standing behind her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Her name is Arixa. She mothered three litters last year that gave me many good hunters. She herself is one of my favored gaurds. Keep her with you and you won't be alone here.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udaughterofshylock.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daughter of Shylock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/19/02 11:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Alone</span><hr size=1> Out of the clearing came another amazon walking through.<br>
<br>
&quot;With or without Arixa, you won't be alone.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cyane said as she came out of the shadows. She looked to Belle and smiled softly.<br>
<br>
&quot;I've always wanted to be apart of a tribe again. You have always had a place in Scynthia, Ephesus and Orio-Pata because of connections. I've only really had Scynthia.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled to Odessa.<br>
<br>
&quot;But since we're practically family, I'd like to make a home here in Paphos. If ya don't mind Dess?&quot;<br>
Cyane smiled. It was true, since her tribe was destroyed so long ago, she longed to find a tribe to call home. What better way to belong than to help return life to a tribe, after hers was destroyed so long ago? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessasaylerloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa Sayler Loire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/20/02 4:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Place to Call Home...</span><hr size=1> Odessa nodded to Aly, smiling.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nai, I'll do my best.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked at the Medallion, and placed it around her neck.<br>
<br>
&quot;Efharisto, eggonaki materas.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked to Arixa and gave the wolf a smile. Scynthians and Wolves had a strong bond, if not most of them, wolves knew how to tell the difference between Amazons and Royalty of the Scynthians.<br>
<br>
She then looked to Cyane, and nodded. She knew how hard it was for Cyane because of her tribe being destroyed, and she knew Paphos would be good for her. She hugged Cyane, and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Welcome Home, Athelfi.&quot; <p>~ Odessa Sayler Loire ~
