<br>
Alysia then turned to Arix and kneeled down.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take care of Odessa my little one.&quot;<br>
She smiled lightly as the large white wolf nuzzled the palm of her hand.<br>
&quot;She's your Queen now. Not me.&quot;<br>
<br>
And she then stood and looked to the three girls.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll see you in Scynthia soon,&quot;<br>
<br>
With that she gave them each a kiss and a hug and turned on her heels heading out the door. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessaofpaphos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/20/02 8:11 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arix</span><hr size=1> She smiled and nodded to Aly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Herete.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked to Cyane, and then to Belle. These girls were important to her...and so was Xenira, believe it or not. Xenira had a great potiential as a Warrior...and an Amazon. Seeing as she held Xena's blood in her veins, she held the potiential as a great Warrior...she knew, deep down, Xenira was an Amazon at heart; whether she believed it...or not.<br>
<br>
&quot;After the Coronation in Scynthia...I'll come back here and fix the place up, it might take me a couple of days...but it's worth it.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then, I'll pick my Second Queen...and my Princess.&quot;<br>
<br>
That...was going to be a hard decision. <p>~* Odessa Sayler Loire *~

