<br>
&quot;You'll make a great Queen Odessa.&quot;<br>
<br>
She smiled lightly but knew that many things pondered inside of Odessa's mind. She glanced between the other two girls and then with a grin she recieved a lightbulb.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have an idea. I want to take you both somewhere I've heard of, we can go there on the way to Scynthia.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cyane was obviously excited about this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ubelleevandaloire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belle EvandaLoire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/23/02 3:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coronation</span><hr size=1> Belle nodded in agreement, smiling.<br>
<br>
&quot;She's right, Dess. You'll be great, and we'll all be around for any help and support that you need.&quot;<br>
<br>
She raised a brow faintly at Cyane's grin and excitement. What was going on in that head of hers?<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright... where is it? Are you sure we can get there if youv'e only heard of it?&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessaofpaphos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/23/02 7:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coronation</span><hr size=1> Odessa grinned to Belle and Cyane, and she laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm with Belle...&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked down to the Wolf that her grandmother gave her, and smiled. <br>
<br>
&quot;I guess it's all right to leave Arixa here...to watch the lands while I'm away...&quot;<br>
<br>
