<br>
&quot;If I know where I want to go, I can get there.&quot;<br>
<br>
She closed her eyes and transported each of them out of the lands.<br>
When they reappeared they were in a dark land. Where the mist grew around them quickly. They stood in a caved area where crystals lit the top of the rocky area.<br>
<br>
Cyane smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're here.&quot;<br>
<br>
She then began to walk down through the cave until she came upon a large pool of water.<br>
<br>
&quot;It does exist.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uodessaofpaphos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#cc9933>(8/28/02 6:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Gift</span><hr size=1> Odessa blinked as they were in the Dark Lands, and she moved with Cyane into the pool and looked down to the water.<br>
